body: We should update the plugin metadata to specify that we support IntelliJ CE and Ultimate. Right now I believe we say that we support all IDE types.

comment_data.body: üëç And while we're at it, we should update other bits too. For example, look at [scala](https://plugins.jetbrains.com/plugin/1347?pr=idea): Issues and website would be great for sure.

OK, so I think this is done? I also added a few links: (Docs point to `getting_started.md`.) We could also inline some basic usage instructions and add a screenshot but I don't feel too strongly. cc @devoncarew @mit-mit
I would rather not inline usage instructions, too many duplicates to maintain.
We should also update the plugin.xml to specify the supported platforms.

> We should also update the plugin.xml to specify the supported platforms.

@alexander-doroshko I did some poking around but couldn't find a way to do this.  Can you advise?

Make sure to read and understand all the info in http://www.jetbrains.org/intellij/sdk/docs/index.html. :) 
I didn't check, but hope that all the info there is correct. Ask me if anything is not clear.

Thanks @alexander-doroshko !

In our case, since we want to specify IDEA CE and Ultimate, is it sufficient to specify shared `java` support?:

```
  <depends>com.intellij.modules.java</depends>
```

(The doc states "(t)he following modules are only available in specific products" but I assume Ultimate is a super-set that contains `com.intellij.modules.java`?)

Yes.
Also check what Android Studio thinks about `<depends>com.intellij.modules.java</depends>` plugins, I guess it may accept it too.

Hmmm.  In that case, is there a good way to specify NOT Android Studio?  Or a better way to specify specifically only UE and CE?

Or maybe it's OK for now since it's on the roadmap...
I may be wrong. According to the docs Android Studio shouldn't match. Please check manually.

title: update the plugin metadata to specify IntelliJ CE and Ultimate
